column5: Well last weekends walleye fishing trip started at leaving oshawa about 4:00am,and getting to sturgeon lake about 1 hour later,well myself and ernie another fellow member hit the lake for some tasty walleyes,we started by fishing our little area we always do by looking for some fresh cabbage& milfoil....and we found it and started to troll along the point just to the outside of the weedbed,and i hit a real nice walleye almost right away,well we just stayed with the programand kept running my electric back & forth across the point and ended up with 5 nice walleyes,and a few lost ones,so we had a pretty good morning and finished up about 11:30 am,because it was getting really hot and by then there was lots of sea-doos and other boats and as usual the lake gets real busy,so thats about that,and had a great walleye fish-fry..and it was great to get some of my ko-man-chi product to use as well it came in handy to,and my pro-staff shirt is real cool too,i like it alot...so here is a few pics of our catch and some nice scenery,and some of the areas where we were fishing on my graph......cheers
Niiiiice going Shawn!!!  Some great shots there!  Seeing the fishfinder/gps shots and fish were pretty cool.  Great shots of the boat as well...it's looking sweet!
Very nice Shawn, some nice golden eyes there.  Joey
Love the fishfinder/GPS shots, nice walleye too.  awesome

Shawn good for you   New boat New shirt you are looking like a PRO.  Great shots of the nice eaters .  Great to see you enjoying the new boat.  I am looking forward to the next report.  I am getting out in the morning .  Thanks MTP
looks like a pretty good day, thanks for sharing.
Nice report Shawn. Looking good in the Ko-Man-Chi attire!!!! I bet those wallies were tasty.MMMMM
and next week your running the camera...
